Continued to rig up 9 5/8" liner handling equipment on rig floor.
Picked up 9 5/8" liner shoe and filled same with 1.40 sg mud and verified integrity of float - OK. Made up and ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner intermediate joint; tube-locked connection.
Made up and ran in hole with float collar joint; Filled liner with 1.40 sg mud and verified integrity of float - OK. Picked up and made up first standard 9 5/8" liner joint. Tube-locked connections.

Changed hose on hydraulic power slips.
Ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner from 330 m to 351 m. Filled every 3rd liner joint with 1.40 sg mud.

Ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner from 351 m to 375 m. Filled every 3rd liner joint with 1.40 sg mud. Unable to released draw work park bakes.
Troubleshot joystick on drillers operating chair. Installed joystick from assistant drillers chair on drillers operating chair.
Ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner from 375 m to 423 Filled every 3rd liner joint with 1.40 sg mud.

Made up circulation swage and DP safety valve. Connected TDS. Circulated liner volume with 2000 lpm, 12 bars. BO circulation swedge and DP safety valve. Recorded weights prior to enter open hole: Up weight 94 tons, down weight 90 tons.

Ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner from 423 m to 424, 4 m. Took weight at 424, 4 m (Casing window). Maximum set down weight 17 tons. Made several attempts to pass through window with various orientations. Established rotation with 5 rpm and 1-2 kNm. Ran liner through window with rotation from 424 m to 435 m. Broke out circulation swage.
Ran in hole with 9 5/8" liner from 435 m to 589 m. Filled every 3rd liner joint with 1,40 sg mud. Filled string. Confirmed remaining liner joints on deck-OK.
Held pre job meeting prior to installing liner hanger.
Changed from 9 5/8" to 5 ½" handling equipment.

P/U 9 5/8" liner hanger assembly from deck, made up MX ball seat/dual wiper plugs to running tool. Held pre-job safety meeting with involved personnel prior to operations. M/U and RIH with liner hanger assembly, set slips and filled liner PBR with drill water. Up/down weights = 117 / 99 tons.
Rigged down casing tong.
RIH with 9 5/8" liner on 5 ½" landing string from 598 m to 984 m; took 13 ton weight at 670 m, 722 m and 852 m.  Washed down from 984 m to 997 m. Tagged bottom with 5 tons. Picked to up weight + 1 m.
Displaced well to 1, 20 sg WBM with 2090 lpm, 46 bars.

M/U cementing head and connected surface line. Broke circulation with 500 lpm / 8 bar, washed down with 9 5/8" liner string from 994 - 997 m. Took up/down weights = 132 /107 tons. Positioned 9 5/8" liner shoe at 995 m.
Gradually increased pump rate to 2000 lpm / 45 bar, circulated open hole volume with 1.20 sg mud. Rotated the liner with 20 rpm and 10-19 kNm.

Reduced pump rate to 200 lpm / 8 bar, dropped setting ball and pumped same down pipe until landed out in ball seat. Set 9 3/8" liner hanger; pressured up to 165 bars for 2 min, than reduced pressure to 70 bars. Set down 25 tons and bled off pressure. Released liner hanger R/T according to Weatherford representative instructions; Pressured up on landing string to 240 bars, held pressure for 2 minutes and then bled off pressure. Pulled to up weight (97 tons) + 1 m to activate the MX ball seat. Set down 20 ton and sheared out ball seat.

Established circulation with 2000 lpm, 44 bar, verified stable returns. Reduced flow rate to 500 lpm, 10 bars and established rotation with 20 rpm, 10-19 kNm, Initial torque needed to establish rotation 39 kNm.

Circulated and conditioned mud prior to liner cementing job; broke circulation and gradually increased pump rate to 2000 lpm / 44 bar, circulated one open hole BU volume. Mud weights in/out = 1.20 sg, no losses seen. Meanwhile held pre-job cement meeting with involved personnel prior to liner cementing operations; reviewed check lists and relevant safety / operational issues. Leak tested surface cementing line to 300 bars for 10 min - OK.
Pumped 20 m3 seawater followed by 20 M3 of 1, 35 sg spacer with rig pumps at 1550 lpm / 28-44 bars. Lined up to pump from cement unit, verified surface routing - OK.

Released lower SSR dart. Mixed and pumped 13, 27 m3 1.92 sg cement slurry with cement unit at 700-900 lpm. Displaced surface cementing lines with 0.89 m3 fresh water. Released top dart. Lined up to pump seawater with rig pumps. Sheared out bottom SSR plug after 2, 9 M3.

Displaced cement slurry in place with rig pumps: Started to pump at 800 lpm / 4 bars, observed bottom wiper plug shear. Increased pump rate to 2100 lpm / 21 - 80 bar, reduced to 600 lpm / 39 bar prior to bumping top plug. Bumped top wiper plug at 1074 strokes, corresponding to 97 % pump efficiency. No losses seen during the entire cementing and displacement operations.
Leak tested 9 5/8" liner to 70 bar above final circulation pressure for 10 min - OK. (Observed a small visual leak on cement head swivel). Bled off pressure and verified float - OK.
Set 9 5/8" TSP liner packer according to Weatherford representative instructions. Set down 28 ton and observed shear at 14 and 21 tons.
Pulled liner hanger R/T out of liner hanger assembly; applied 50 bar pressure on pipe prior to operation, confirmed pressure drop. Circulated with 500 lpm, 6 bar while pulling out of PBR.
Held pre job meeting. Laid out cement head with 1 single of DP below.
Installed 2 x sponge wiper balls in landing string. Circulated at 3100 lpm / 38 bar with sea water to clean out landing string and possible excess cement; no cement seen in returns.
Pulled out of hole with landing string from 400 m to 370 m.
Water u-tube out of pipe. Connected TDS and continued circulating the hole clean with 3100 lpm, 40 bar.
Pulled out of hole from 370 m to surface.

Cleaned out rat hole below casing shoe with 1600 lpm, 55 bar, WOB 0 - 1 tons, 30 rpm, 8 kNm. Simultaneously: Held pre job meeting prior to displace well from SW to 1.28 sg Soludrill mud.

Adjusted down weight on hanger to 10 tons. Released running tool with 8 right hand turns. Attempted to pick up 1 meter but took full string weight. Picked up 3.8 m to extend packer actuator dogs above the PBR. Sat down 30 ton on PBR to set liner hanger packer, observed booth 2 shears. Pulled running tool out of PBR.
Prepared pit space and started mixing of 1.03 sg NaCl brine. Not done earlier due to pit capacity.
Continued mixing 1.03 sg NaCl brine. Meanwhile performed general rig maintenance.
Displaced 9 5/8" and 13 3/8" casing to 1.03 sg NaCl with 3000 lpm, 63 bars.

Pumped 9.6 m³ of citric acid, 1.06 sg, displaced with 12.6 m³ 1.03 sg brine at 1500 lpm, 27 bars.
Observed well on trip tank. Gained 0.36 M3/hr for the first half hour due to thermal expansion, then levelled of and stabilized.

Pulled the upper cup into the blank pipe and swabbed the well 11 times with 30 m strokes (1153-1123 m) 30 m/min. Ran back to 1187 m. Opened the stand pipe valve. Pumped 0.5 m³ down DP and displaced clean acid into well bore. Closed stand pipe valve. Pulled out of hole until upper swab cups above screens.
Monitored well on trip tank for losses. Loss rate 1.5 - 2 M3/min.
Stopped filling the hole from trip tank and let fluid level in annulus drop to equilibrium.
Ran in hole to 1159 m. Removed hydraulic power slips and installed master bushing. Ran in hole from 1159 m to 1187 m.
Pumped 6.2 m³ of citric acid, 1.06 sg, displaced with 12.8 m³ 1.03 sg brine at 1500 lpm, 29 bars. No return seen.
Laid out double DP, installed side entry sub and Kelly cock on string.
Held pre job meeting. Performed cut and slip of drill line. Broke bolts on dead mans anchor gear box.
Changed out broken bolts in gearbox on dead mans anchor.
Continued cut and slip operation. Found lock pin on dead mans anchor to be broken.
Repaired lock pin on dead mans anchor.
Reset and tested anti collision system.
BO side entry sub and Kelly cock.  Installed double DP. Placed upper cup into the blank pipe.
Pumped/bull-headed 30 M3 of 1.03 sg NaCl brine. 400 lpm, 4 bar. Increased flow rate to 1490 lpm, 28 bars after 15 M3 pumped.
Located lower swab cup inside the blank pipe and pumped/bull-headed 20 M3 of 1.03 sg NaCl packer fluid. 1500 lpm, 22 bar.
Pulled out of hole from 985 m to 930 m. (Bull nose above the screen hanger).
Mixed 90 M3 of 1.03 sg packer fluid. Not done earlier due to pit capacity.
Filled annulus with 85 M3 1.03 sg packer fluid. Loss rate decreased from 2 M3/min to 40 l/min after having displaced in 85 M3 of completion fluid.
Discussed further operation, could not find any surface reason causing the sudden decrease in loss rate. Decided to re-swab the well.
Ran in hole from 930 m to 995 m. Filled pipe and observed communication to trip tank, indicating flow past upper cup in blank pipe.

Swabbed the well 10 times with 30 m strokes (991-961 m) 30 m/min. Pulled out of hole to 930 m. (Bull nose above the screen hanger). Loss rate 1.2 M3/min. Stopped filling the hole from trip tank and let fluid level in annulus drop to equilibrium.
Pulled out of hole from 930 m to 270 m. Filled hole with 2 M3/10 stand pulled.
Changed inserts in hydraulic power slips. Discovered that eye for safety wire on elevator inserts was damaged.
Welded on new eye for safety wire on elevator insert. Meanwhile greased dolly.
Was not able to rack back 3 1/5" DP in fingerboard. Initialized system-OK.
Continued pulling out of hole and lay out swab cup assemblies from 270 m to surface.
Cleaned and tidied rig floor. Changed inserts in elevator.
Made up wear bushing running tool. Removed master bushing.
Ran in hole. Engaged to wear bushing. Pulled out of hole with wear bushing. LO wear bushing and wear bushing running tool.
Made up riser/wellhead wash tool. Ran in hole and washed wellhead area with 1500 lpm, 5 bars. Past wellhead area 3 times. Pulled out and BO wellhead wash tool.
Made up and racked back tubing hanger assembly.
Held pre job meeting prior to RU for running ESP. Rigged up and spot equipment.
Rigged up and spot ESP equipment.

Picked up and made up ESP assembly 1 and 2. Connected control lines to motor. Made up ¼" hydraulic line from Multisensor gauge. Pumped oil into the motor by a hand pump. Serviced the motor and evacuated the air. Connected up the electrical cable to the motor and tested out same. Installed protectolizer clamp on the base of the motor.
Picked up and made up ESP assembly 3(ESP pump).
Continued to make up ESP pump to protector. Installed clamp on ESP pump.
Picked up and made up ESP assembly 4(ESP discharge pressure assembly).
Held pre job meeting.
Picked up and made up bolt-on discharge head XO joint.

Picked up and made up first 7 5/8" tubing joint. Adjusted and aligned casing tong. Held pre job meeting prior to install hydraulic power slips. Installed clamp on tubing for protection while installing hydraulic power slips. Installed hydraulic power slips. Removed clamp.

LO 3 joints of tubing due to bad connections.
Ran 7 5/8" tubing from 81 m to 105 m.
LO 1 joint of tubing due to bad connection.
Ran 7 5/8" tubing from 105 m to 117 m. LO 2 joints of tubing due to bad connections.
Discussed further operation. Decided to clean all pins and boxes, check threads and re-dope the tubing.
Ran 7 5/8" tubing from 105 m to 176 m.
LO 2 joints of tubing due to bad connections.
Ran 7 5/8" tubing from 164 m to 273 m.
Ran 7 5/8" tubing from 273 m to 357 m.
Performed electrical check of down hole system. Changed inserts in elevator. Confirmed remaining liner joints on deck-OK.
Made up tubing hanger/swivel assembly.
Broke FAST connection. Oriented the tubing hanger. Made up FAST connection. Cleared rig floor of redundant equipment.
Installed clamps on tubing for protection while removing hydraulic power slips and installing master bushing. Removed hydraulic power slips.
Installed penetrator incluning seals through hanger.
Schlumberger prepared for electrical cable splice.
Spaced out and spliced cable.
Attached peneterator to hanger.
Pressure tested peneterator o-ring to 69 bar / 10 min. OK.
Tested electric cable. TBT prior to pull mastrer bushing.
Ran hanger through rotary table. Had to remove master bushing.
RIH and landed hanger 20,92m in on landing string.
Checked electrical cable, OK.
Disconnected Tubing Hanger Running Tool and  POOH with same.
TBT prior to remove casing tong.

B/O and L/D Running Tool on deck.

TBT prior to pull diverter.
Pulled diverter and L/D same on deck.
Rigged up double set of slings for pulling riser, held TBT.
Installed slings and attempted to pull riser. No go.
Continued attempts to pull riser. Moved riser, adjusted bolts, tried to re-position lock ring.
Could not disconnect riser from well head. Contacted town, trouble shot.
Troubleshot problems with lock ring between riser and wellhead. TBT with on comming crew.
Adjusted release bolts to press lock ring in centre. Took 3 ton over pull, slacked off to neutral. Continued to adjust stroke of bolts. Riser free.
Picked up riser, installed master bushing.
TBT prior to L/D riser.
L/D riser on deck.
Prepared wellhead for spacer spool.
Checked yellow tugger wire, OK. TBT prior to installation of spacer spool.

Removed and L/D lifting equipment. Cleaned rigfloor and wellhead area. Removed handrails on the weatherdeck.
Leak tested cable peneterator seals in tubing bonnet to 69 bar / 10 min. OK. Meanwhile held TBT prior to disconnect Kelly hose.
Leak tested bonnet cavity to 69 bar / 10 min. OK. Meanwhile started to disconnect kelly hose. END OF OPERATION F - 9A. WELL HANDED OVER TO PRODUCTION.

Well handed over from production. Held pre-job meeting for removal of flowline and ball valve.
Lifted off F-9 hatch cover in moonpool.
Disconnected flowline from F-9. Secured same on XMT deck.
Prepared to remove ball valve from flow head assembly.
Prepared to pull diverter.
Performed TBT for pulling diverter and securing same to DP in derrick.
Removed master bushings and outer ring, installed handrails around rotary. Installed diverter lifting eyes and connected lifting bridle.
Pulled diverter and secured same to DP in derrick.
Performed TBT for removing ball valve from spacer spool and pulling spacer spool and tubing bonnet to drill floor.
Removed ball valve from spacer spool and secured same on XMT deck.
Rigged up to pull spacer spool and tubing bonnet to drill floor. Made up release bolts on tubing bonnet.  Meanwhile Production dept shut-in nearby wells according to SimOps procedure.
Attempted to lift spacer spool and tubing bonnet without success, +/- 3 ton overpull. Slacked off weight and retried several times. No movement.

Reconfigured rig up and installed a 5 ton chain hoist for better control over weight taken. Simultaneously loosened ALT-2 release bolts. Attempted to lift tubing bonnet and spacer spool, 4 ton overpull, little movement observed, but still not free.
Removed chain hoist and re-attached double slings to ensure straight-up lift. Pulled up, backed out release bolts and pulled tubing bonnet free. Covered tubing hanger with bucket.
Lifted flow head assembly to drill floor, landed same on HTS. L/O assembly on deck. Meanwhile cleaned and greased wellhead.
Performed TBT for running riser
Lifted riser to HTS. Installed shackles and slings for handling riser through rotary
Stop in operation due to call from Production dept regarding possible leak on well F-14. Waited until Production dept verified no leak.
Lifted riser using TDS, tugger and crane. Tailed riser in to well center and disconnected crane and tugger.
Ran riser through rotary and landed off in WH. Took 8 ton overpull to confirm latch.
Build scaffholding in moonpool to remove handling slings from surface riser.
Disconnected and removed slings/shackles from riser and pulled same to rig floor. Removed slings from TDS chains.
R/D scaffholding in moonpool. Meanwhile prepared for lifting diverter.

Continued troubleshoot loss off pressure. Narrowed causes to a open needle valve on surface wellhead. Closed needle valve.

Lined up cement unit to drill string. Pressured up well to 11 bar reference pressure. Pressured up to 34 bar using 101 litre. Pressure dropped and stabilized at 24 bar.
